    • Method Detail

      • onResize

        public void onResize()
        This method must be called whenever the logo's size has been modified. This is typically the result of the browser window being resized and is typically handled by the owning ViewPanel, View or some other implementor of the ProvidesResize interface. Because a resize involves getting and setting the size of the Image widget, the image must already be loaded. Consequently, if isLoaded() returns false, a LoadHandler is created and onResize() rescheduled to occur when Image.getWidth/getHeight will succeed.

        onResize in interface com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.RequiresResize
